article.headline: Long's 14 lead Vermont past Dartmouth 64-53

images.name: TJ Hurley fights off defender for and-1
images.caption: TJ Hurley fights off defender for and-1

article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- — TJ Long's 14 points helped Vermont defeat Dartmouth 64-53 on Wednesday night. Long shot 5 for 8, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc for the Catamounts (6-2). TJ Hurley scored 12 points and added six rebounds. Aaron Deloney was 3 of 11 shooting, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 4 from the line to finish with nine points. Dusan Neskovic led the way for the Big Green (1-4) with 17 points and two steals. Brandon Mitchell-Day added 10 points and 10 rebounds for Dartmouth. In addition, Jayden Williams had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
